quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  30,20,One of His signs is that He created you from dust and- lo and behold!- you became human and scattered far and wide
  30,21,"Another of His signs is that He created spouses from among yourselves for you to live with in tranquillity: He ordained love and kindness between you. There truly are signs in this for those who reflect"
  30,22,"Another of His signs is the creation of the heavens and earth, and the diversity of your languages and colours. There truly are signs in this for those who know"
  30,23,"Among His signs are your sleep, by night and by day, and your seeking His bounty. There truly are signs in this for those who can hear"
  30,24,"Among His signs, too, are that He shows you the lightning that terrifies and inspires hope; that He sends water down from the sky to restore the earth to life after death. There truly are signs in this for those who use their reason"
  30,25,"Among His signs, too, is the fact that the heavens and the earth stand firm by His command. In the end, you will all emerge when He calls you from the earth"
  30,26,"Everyone in the heavens and earth belongs to Him, and all are obedient to Him"
  30,27,"He is the One who originates creation and will do it again- this is even easier for Him. He is above all comparison in the heavens and earth; He is the Almighty, the All Wise"